values: Everyone knows everybody else. It is quite funny. Everyone loves my best friend, everyone but me of course. Another friend is in love with a whore, a whore my dealer has fucked. So many stories flying around, born from the mouths of the ever growing circle. It will all be set right when the potheads meet tonight; with some minor alterations. My, my. Something seems to be missing...something or someone. Perhaps I should travel to the puppet burn ward, and visit my peers.

There's no earthly way of knowing, Which direction we are going. There's no knowing where we are rowing, or which way the river's flowing. Is it raining? Is it snowing? Is a hurricane a-blowing? Bleh! Not a speck of light is showing, So the danger must be growing. Are the fires of hell a glowing? Is the grisly reaper mowing? Yes! The danger must be growing, For the rowers keep on rowing. And they're certainly not showing, Any signs that they are slowing!

Stop the boat.

I suppose I should be grateful; I learned to swim.
Don't say you don't deserve what life offers you. It might be listening, and may not be so generous the next time.

There is a funny situation to be found when you force others to admit they care about you. Especially when they know, that you know, they do care about your general well being.
It's a pity I'm not very appreciative. And not designed to make any sense.

Apathy switch engaged. Robots can't be hurt. Beauty is in the eye of the beholder.

I'm only trying to sound like a decent person.

Yay for feeble attempts.
